The current integration is still using the legacy Microsoft Teams incoming webhook URL from Databricks. Although Microsoft had announced the retirement of this webhook mechanism, the existing URL is currently still functioning, so our Databricks alerts continue to be delivered successfully.

Microsoft's recommended replacement is the Teams Workflows-based integration, which uses Power Automate. I have already discussed this approach with Daniel. However, implementing the new workflow-based solution requires the appropriate Power Automate licensing.

For now, we will continue using the existing webhook integration while it remains operational. Once the Power Automate licensing is in place, we can migrate to the supported Teams Workflows solution to ensure the integration is aligned with Microsoft's current recommendations and remains supported going forward.
